00:35:45,646 --> 00:35:49,649
<i>Derek, what can you tell us
about the investigation so far?</i>

480
00:35:49,650 --> 00:35:52,402
[Derek] <i>We understand
that First Desk, Ingrid Tearney,</i>

481
00:35:52,486 --> 00:35:55,030
<i>will be debriefing
the Home Secretary later on today</i>

482
00:35:55,614 --> 00:36:00,493
<i>on what has been a successful operation
to rescue kidnapped student Hassan Ahmed.</i>

483
00:36:00,494 --> 00:36:02,912
[Hassan] <i>I'd just like to say thank you</i>

484
00:36:02,913 --> 00:36:07,542
<i>to the police a-and the security services</i>

485
00:36:07,543 --> 00:36:10,504
<i>for their really, really incredible work.</i>

486
00:36:11,004 --> 00:36:13,840
<i>We understand he was freed
shortly after 7:00 a.m. this morning</i>

487
00:36:13,841 --> 00:36:18,094
<i>by an MI5 operation in which
two of the kidnappers were killed,</i>

488
00:36:18,095 --> 00:36:20,597
<i>and a further man remains in custody.</i>

489
00:36:24,560 --> 00:36:27,228
Well, I suppose well done, us.

490
00:36:27,229 --> 00:36:30,691
[Min chuckles] I've got a bottle of wine
in the desk if anyone wants to celebrate.

491
00:36:31,567 --> 00:36:33,360
Celebrate? What?

492
00:36:34,528 --> 00:36:35,528
Well, we saved him.

493
00:36:35,529 --> 00:36:38,114
How? You... You were useless.

494
00:36:38,115 --> 00:36:39,449
I tracked the van.

495
00:36:39,533 --> 00:36:42,160
Yeah, to Harwich,
where the Dogs were waiting for him.

496
00:36:42,244 --> 00:36:43,703
Thanks to me squeezing Lady Di.

497
00:36:43,704 --> 00:36:45,663
Yeah, well, I actually did save him.

498
00:36:45,664 --> 00:36:47,809
Whilst he was being shot at
and threatened with an axe.

499
00:36:47,833 --> 00:36:50,794
The kid saved himself, with a rock.

500
00:36:50,878 --> 00:36:52,838
I just love these team talks, I really do.

501
00:36:54,423 --> 00:36:56,341
Come on, everyone. Back to work!

502
00:36:56,425 --> 00:36:57,550
It's Saturday.

503
00:36:57,551 --> 00:36:59,385
[Jackson] Then everyone piss off!

504
00:36:59,386 --> 00:37:00,470
Drink?

505
00:37:03,432 --> 00:37:05,100
- [sniffles]
- Got a lead on Sid.

506
00:37:13,942 --> 00:37:15,777
Okay. Wine.

507
00:37:20,157 --> 00:37:23,201
Right. Well, I hope you don't mind,
um, a <i>vin de</i> Tesco.

508
00:37:23,202 --> 00:37:26,121
[chuckles] Yeah. I'll get some glasses.

509
00:37:27,122 --> 00:37:28,957
- All right.
- Actually, you know what, Min?

510
00:37:29,041 --> 00:37:34,880
I, uh... I am... I'm shattered.
I'm gonna crash. Sorry.

511
00:37:35,839 --> 00:37:36,965
Yeah. Sure. Sure.

512
00:37:37,049 --> 00:37:38,258
[Louisa] It's been a long day.

513
00:37:38,759 --> 00:37:39,885
Yeah. No, I'm tired too.

514
00:37:44,181 --> 00:37:48,435
But I am free tonight for some drinks or...

515
00:37:49,311 --> 00:37:50,728
maybe some food or something.

516
00:37:50,729 --> 00:37:51,813
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah?

517
00:37:51,897 --> 00:37:54,190
Great. Sounds good. Um...

518
00:37:54,191 --> 00:37:56,067
Yeah, I'm just thinking, uh, how about...

519
00:37:56,068 --> 00:37:59,112
Well, how about I just actually
stop talking before I spoil everything?

520
00:37:59,196 --> 00:38:00,197
Smart.

521
00:38:19,466 --> 00:38:21,760
- [Roddy] See?
- See what? I don't see anything.

522
00:38:21,844 --> 00:38:22,844
[Roddy] Exactly.

523
00:38:22,845 --> 00:38:25,388
There's no record of her
ever having been at the hospital.

524
00:38:25,389 --> 00:38:27,724
And, when I pop through
my own private backdoor

525
00:38:27,808 --> 00:38:29,100
into MI5's database,

526
00:38:29,101 --> 00:38:31,227
there's no record of her whatsoever.

527
00:38:31,228 --> 00:38:32,729
So what does that mean?

528
00:38:34,273 --> 00:38:38,693
It means, far as you know,
and even as far as Roddy Ho knows,

529
00:38:38,694 --> 00:38:41,655
which is a fuck of a lot farther
than anyone has ever known,

530
00:38:42,239 --> 00:38:44,324
there is gonna be
no funeral or memorial service

531
00:38:44,408 --> 00:38:46,660
or so much as drinks at the pub
for Sidonie Baker.

532
00:38:48,537 --> 00:38:51,373
'Cause no one
named Sidonie Baker ever existed.

533
00:38:58,547 --> 00:39:01,133
So... [sighs] ...in return?

534
00:39:03,594 --> 00:39:04,594
In return for what?

535
00:39:04,595 --> 00:39:07,848
For letting you know
she might still be alive somewhere.

536
00:39:10,184 --> 00:39:11,185
[River] You wanna know?

537
00:39:15,397 --> 00:39:16,899
All right. Um...

538
00:39:18,192 --> 00:39:20,861
Well... [clears throat, clicks tongue]

539
00:39:21,862 --> 00:39:25,240
thing is, Roddy,
you're in Slough House...

540
00:39:33,999 --> 00:39:35,167
because you're too good.

541
00:39:37,169 --> 00:39:39,170
You showed everyone else up.

542
00:39:39,171 --> 00:39:41,798
Made them all look bad,
so they shoved you in here.

543
00:39:46,637 --> 00:39:47,638
Figures.

544
00:39:49,389 --> 00:39:52,142
[sighs] Tried to cage me up...

545
00:39:53,936 --> 00:39:55,771
but you can't cage a dragon.

546
00:40:01,568 --> 00:40:04,738
[person on phone speaks indistinctly]

547
00:40:06,949 --> 00:40:08,700
All right. [sniffles]

548
00:40:42,651 --> 00:40:43,735
[sighs]

549
00:40:51,493 --> 00:40:52,494
[clears throat]

550
00:40:58,333 --> 00:40:59,542
[door opens]

551
00:40:59,543 --> 00:41:01,461
[footsteps]

552
00:41:20,814 --> 00:41:24,526
Natasha. You need to bring me in
and put me on air.

553
00:41:26,236 --> 00:41:28,738
But what you're seeing
on the news is bullshit!

554
00:41:28,739 --> 00:41:31,491
Establishment cover-up bullshit.

555
00:41:33,035 --> 00:41:34,036
Well, send a car.

556
00:41:34,870 --> 00:41:39,082
[sighs] I can get there quicker by myself.
Uh, I can be there in...

557
00:41:42,252 --> 00:41:45,004
[pedestrian 1] Jesus.
You all right, mate? You all right?

558
00:41:45,005 --> 00:41:46,840
[pedestrian 2] Hold on, hold on, hold on.

559
00:41:46,924 --> 00:41:48,425
[people clamoring]

560
00:41:57,559 --> 00:41:58,560
Diana.

561
00:41:59,061 --> 00:42:00,687
- Jackson.
- [exhales sharply]

562
00:42:01,772 --> 00:42:02,814
Well done.

563
00:42:02,898 --> 00:42:06,276
Managed to keep the name Alan Black
out of the headlines.

564
00:42:06,360 --> 00:42:08,111
Never existed.

565
00:42:08,737 --> 00:42:11,073
You mean Dermot Radcliffe, Son of Albion.

566
00:42:12,199 --> 00:42:13,200
[sighs]

567
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:20,248
Hassan didn't overhear anything
that might poke holes in that?

568
00:42:20,249 --> 00:42:21,333
Possibly.

569
00:42:21,834 --> 00:42:23,460
But his student debt's been cleared,

570
00:42:23,544 --> 00:42:26,922
and his comedy club is about to receive
a large anonymous donation.

571
00:42:29,758 --> 00:42:31,593
Do you know what boils my piss?

572
00:42:33,011 --> 00:42:34,012
Is that you won.

573
00:42:35,055 --> 00:42:38,558
Boy saved, you get to look like a hero.

574
00:42:38,559 --> 00:42:40,811
Made your boss look even more of a hero.

575
00:42:42,479 --> 00:42:44,799
What are you gonna tell Standish
about what's in that file?

576
00:42:48,110 --> 00:42:50,195
And the photographs on Cartwright's phone?

577
00:42:51,154 --> 00:42:52,155
Deleted.

578
00:42:52,698 --> 00:42:54,116
Can I trust you on that?

579
00:42:56,118 --> 00:42:58,662
Can I trust you
you didn't make a copy of this?

580
00:43:00,122 --> 00:43:02,832
I'm assuming you don't want
Struan Loy back.

581
00:43:02,833 --> 00:43:06,753
[sighs] Well, you put him
in a very difficult position, Diana.

582
00:43:06,837 --> 00:43:10,507
Betray me, get back to the Park.
Or don't and be cast into the wilderness.

583
00:43:10,591 --> 00:43:12,550
He betrayed you, so wilderness.

584
00:43:12,551 --> 00:43:13,677
Fuck yeah.

585
00:43:14,761 --> 00:43:16,096
And River Cartwright?

586
00:43:39,244 --> 00:43:41,621
I'm sorry, but what did you expect?

587
00:43:41,622 --> 00:43:45,625
Well, Stansted wasn't me.
And we rescued Hassan.

588
00:43:45,626 --> 00:43:50,880
So... clean slate back at the Park
didn't feel like too much of a stretch.

589
00:43:50,881 --> 00:43:51,965
So you thought, what?

590
00:43:52,049 --> 00:43:54,259
Diana Taverner would confess her sins

591
00:43:54,343 --> 00:43:58,638
in order to benefit your career
while simultaneously destroying her own?

592
00:43:58,639 --> 00:44:00,390
Tad naive, wouldn't you say?

593
00:44:00,933 --> 00:44:04,102
Moscow rules, watch your back.
London rules, cover your arse.

594
00:44:04,186 --> 00:44:06,980
Yeah. [laughs]

595
00:44:07,064 --> 00:44:11,652
I seem to have covered her arse,
while she stabbed me straight in the back.

596
00:44:12,361 --> 00:44:15,822
[David] I will permit one evening
of indulgent self-recrimination,

597
00:44:15,906 --> 00:44:20,035
which will end when I nod off
after approximately 20 minutes.

598
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:23,872
You need to get your head down.

599
00:44:23,956 --> 00:44:28,877
Keep your nose clean, and then maybe,
just maybe, there's a way back in.

600
00:44:32,214 --> 00:44:33,548
Oh, come on.

601
00:44:33,549 --> 00:44:36,343
Even the best spies have
their time in the cold.

602
00:44:37,511 --> 00:44:40,514
Smiley was always coming back
from redundancy.

603
00:44:41,515 --> 00:44:45,143
- Hmm? [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

604
00:44:50,148 --> 00:44:51,149
[grunts]

605
00:45:57,966 --> 00:45:59,176
[Catherine echoing] <i>Charles.</i>

606
00:46:01,178 --> 00:46:03,156
[Diana] <i>There are things
about Charles Partner's death</i>

607
00:46:03,180 --> 00:46:04,973
<i>that Lamb hasn't told you.</i>

608
00:46:22,199 --> 00:46:23,616
What was Taverner going to tell me?

609
00:46:23,617 --> 00:46:27,328
[chuckles] For fuck's sake.
It's... It's Saturday.

610
00:46:27,329 --> 00:46:29,747
Haven't you got
other people's cats to steal?

611
00:46:29,748 --> 00:46:32,417
What aren't you telling me
about Charles's death?

612
00:46:32,501 --> 00:46:33,502
Nothing.

613
00:46:34,545 --> 00:46:38,757
I don't believe you.
I should have read the signs. Should I?

614
00:46:41,718 --> 00:46:44,221
[sighs, clicks tongue]

615
00:46:45,931 --> 00:46:47,182
Tell me. What don't I...

616
00:46:47,266 --> 00:46:48,767
I gave him the gun.

617
00:46:54,523 --> 00:46:55,524
Why?

618
00:46:59,570 --> 00:47:02,614
[sighs] Because he asked for one.

619
00:47:05,492 --> 00:47:06,577
And he was my friend.

620
00:47:13,542 --> 00:47:15,627
This was after the Wall came down.

621
00:47:19,464 --> 00:47:22,259
Cold War scores were being settled.

622
00:47:23,010 --> 00:47:26,513
And he told me
he'd seen some old, unfriendly faces.

623
00:47:26,597 --> 00:47:28,098
I thought he was being paranoid,

624
00:47:28,182 --> 00:47:31,310
but... you know, what if I was wrong,
and he ended...

625
00:47:37,107 --> 00:47:38,775
Well, it threw my mojo off.

626
00:47:41,820 --> 00:47:46,241
Put a dent in my armor. [sighs]

627
00:47:49,161 --> 00:47:54,833
I-I didn't want to be in the field.
I wanted to be a civilian even less.

628
00:47:58,587 --> 00:48:02,841
So... this is why I asked for this place.

629
00:48:06,970 --> 00:48:10,933
Somewhere where I could run out the clock.

630
00:48:13,268 --> 00:48:15,521
Nothing matters, and no one gets hurt.

631
00:48:27,157 --> 00:48:29,618
Oh, come on.
One of us has to leave the room now.

632
00:48:32,621 --> 00:48:34,206
And I'm just too fucking tired.

633
00:48:46,593 --> 00:48:47,594
[sighs]

634
00:49:11,493 --> 00:49:15,247
[classical opera music playing]

635
00:49:27,843 --> 00:49:28,844
[groans]

636
00:49:51,325 --> 00:49:53,702
Ha! [grunts]

637
00:50:01,168 --> 00:50:03,170
[panting]

638
00:50:31,949 --> 00:50:33,951
[panting]

639
00:50:34,785 --> 00:50:35,786
Is it done?

640
00:50:39,831 --> 00:50:42,292
Yeah. [panting]

641
00:50:44,253 --> 00:50:45,879
And so am I.

642
00:50:46,922 --> 00:50:48,131
If they find out...

643
00:50:51,593 --> 00:50:54,846
How would they find out, David?
It's just you and me in this car.

644
00:50:54,847 --> 00:50:57,057
They are rather good at their job.

645
00:50:59,601 --> 00:51:02,980
Well, I hope for your sake they don't.

646
00:51:37,723 --> 00:51:40,350
["Strange Game" playing]

647
00:52:01,371 --> 00:52:04,040
[Louisa] <i>When an agent dies,
everything has to be considered.</i>

648
00:52:04,041 --> 00:52:07,211
Well, he left a note on his phone.
"Cicada."

649
00:52:07,794 --> 00:52:10,338
[River] <i>Sleeper agents embedded
in British society.</i>

650
00:52:10,339 --> 00:52:12,424
We call them dead lions.

651
00:52:12,508 --> 00:52:14,968
[Diana] <i>Lamb, I do not need you
digging around in the past.</i>

652
00:52:15,677 --> 00:52:17,929
[Roddy]
<i>Maybe the Cicadas have been reactivated,</i>

653
00:52:17,930 --> 00:52:19,472
<i>and maybe more people are gonna die.</i>

654
00:52:19,473 --> 00:52:21,225
I'm putting you in the field.

655
00:52:21,934 --> 00:52:23,769
- What?
- It's exciting.

656
00:52:26,021 --> 00:52:27,522
Be careful, River.

657
00:52:27,523 --> 00:52:32,402
The Russians have an incredible capacity
for pain and sacrifice. And grudges.

658
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:35,738
<i>We had a traitor right at the top.</i>

659
00:52:35,739 --> 00:52:37,782
[River]
<i>Thousands of people, they're gonna die.</i>

660
00:52:37,783 --> 00:52:39,868
Paperwork's gonna be a ballache.

661
00:52:40,452 --> 00:52:43,914
[Russian] <i>I want the professional
humiliation of you and your team.</i>

662
00:52:44,998 --> 00:52:47,751
[Jackson] <i>My team have already
humiliated themselves.</i>

663
00:52:49,253 --> 00:52:51,129
That's why they're my team.

664
00:52:55,300 --> 00:52:57,344
["Strange Game" playing]
